Required documents:
Identification document of the applicant;
Public service number or reference on not receiving a public service number;
Certificate of ownership of the real estate to be renovated (copy);
Identification document (copy) of the co-owners of the real estate to be renovated;
Ownership document (copy) of real estate, offered as collateral;
Identification document (copy) of co-owners of the real estate, offered as collateral;
Marriage certificates (if married) of co-owners of the real estate, offered as collateral;
Reference from the applicant's employer* about the average monthly income received by the applicant (calculated over the last 12 months);
Estimate of required current and/or capital renovation works and costs, filled in by the customer;
If required, other documents may be requested.
The issue date of the documents at the time of acceptance shall not exceed 15 days.
Depending on the circumstances, additional documents and information may be required.
* Reference shall include the customer's monthly net salary/income after taxes, work address, phone numbers, signature and stamp of the referring organization manager, outgoing date of issue.
